display="inline"><![CDATA[u\colon  Y_\bullet \to  X_\bullet ]]></fr:tex> be a morphism of topological simplicial spaces, with cone <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C(u)]]></fr:tex>.
    Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> be an abelian sheaf on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_\bullet ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> an abelian sheaf on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_\bullet ]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  G\to  F]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u]]></fr:tex>-morphism.
    The cone <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C(f)]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is an abelian sheaf on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C(u)]]></fr:tex>, and we set

